    <p>Isaiah Hartwell writes picture books for the kids who feel things deeply — the patient ones, the loud-world-overwhelmed ones, the ones who see the world a little differently and make it more beautiful for it.</p>

    <p>Made Out of Clay Productions began with a simple belief: that every child deserves to see themselves on the page, exactly as they are. That belief grew into three series —</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>At Sunny's Table</strong> — a gentle sloth family learning patience, quiet, and belonging.</li>
      <li><strong>Just the Way You Are</strong> — identity-first stories of neurodiversity and inclusion, inspired by a real boy named Clayton.</li>
      <li><strong>The Kingdom of Judea</strong> — Caleb and the Cubs on an epic lion-kingdom adventure about courage and home.</li>
    </ul>

